&gt; I&#39;m trying to get all my junit tests in a suite to run, even if
&gt; there are one or more failures/errors.  Afterwards, I want the build
&gt; to fail if there were any failures or errors.

See the failureproperty and errorproperty attributes of &lt;junit&gt;.
Basically you set the halton* properties to false and use those
properties together with a conditional &lt;fail&gt; on the failureproperty
at the point where you want your build to fail.

From Ant&#39;s own build file (current CVS):

    &lt;junit printsummary=&quot;${junit.summary}&quot; haltonfailure=&quot;${test.haltonfailure}&quot;
           filtertrace=&quot;${junit.filtertrace}&quot;
           fork=&quot;${junit.fork}&quot;
           failureproperty=&quot;tests.failed&quot;&gt;
      &lt;BIG-SNIP/&gt;
    &lt;/junit&gt;
    &lt;fail if=&quot;tests.failed&quot;&gt;At least one test has failed.&lt;/fail&gt;

